    <h1>1. Describe the ways to open developers console in Mozilla Firefox and
Safari.</h1>
    <p>To open the developer console in Mozilla Firefox, you can use keyboard shortcuts (Ctrl + Shift + I or F12;Press Cmd + Option + I) or Right-click anywhere on a webpage, select "Inspect Element", and the developer tools window will open with the console tab selected.</p>

<p>To open the developer console in Safari, you can also use keyboard shortcuts (Press Cmd + Option + C) or Right-click anywhere on a webpage and select "Inspect Element", then navigate to the "Console" tab in the developer tools window.</p>
    
     <h2>2. What way of including internal links into the HTML page you would consider generally preferable: absolute or relative links?</h2>
    <p>The preferred way to include internal links in an HTML page generally depends on the specific use case and website structure. Relative links are more portable and easier to manage when moving or copying files within the same directory or to a different directory. Absolute links contain the full URL, including the domain name, which can cause issues if the domain changes or if the website is migrated to a different server. Relative links work seamlessly on local development environments and staging servers without having to change the URLs. This makes the development process smoother and prevents broken links. </p>
    
      <h4>3. What is the difference between JPG, GIF and PNG formats?</h4>
    <p>Each image format has its own strengths and weaknesses, and the choice of format depends on the specific requirements of the image, such as quality, file size, transparency, and color depth. JPG is best for photographs, GIF for simple animations and images with solid colors, and PNG for images with sharp edges and transparency.</p>
    
     <h1>4. What is WEBP image type?</h1>
    <p> WebP is a powerful and efficient image format that offers numerous benefits for website performance and user experience. As web technologies continue to evolve, WebP is increasingly becoming a popular choice for optimizing images on the web.</p>

 <h1>5. What is SVG?</h1>
    <p>SVG is a versatile and powerful image format that offers numerous benefits for web design, including scalability, resolution independence, interactivity, and accessibility. It has become a popular choice for creating icons, logos, illustrations, charts, and other graphics on the web.</p>
    
